translated: Brundin, Sigfrid Emanuel, LL.B., lawyer, Gothenburg, b. 19/4/98 in Backa, Gothenburg and Bohuslän County, son of civil servants Wilhelm B. and Helena Koliinius. Married in 1928 to Karin Lundahl, with whom he had two children: Lars, born in 1930, and Eva, born in 1933. Brundin completed his high school education in 1917, earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in 1920, and earned his law degree in 1929. He has been practicing as a lawyer in Gothenburg since 1931 and became a member of the Swedish Bar Association in 1935.
